div.div: Comedy, Horror, Slice of Life, Supernatural

She can see dead people…she just chooses to ignore them. That’s Miko’s plan, anyway, but it doesn’t seem to be working for her in this love letter to the horror genre that will send shivers down your spine—and occasionally tickle your funny bone.
(Source: Funimation)

Thwarting a hijacking with the beautiful, silver-haired detective, Siesta, transforms Kimihiko’s young life. Their success kicks off years of crime-solving and confronting syndicates around the world—until Siesta dies. Left with questions, Kimihiko moves on. But now, a new case may open healed wounds as it connects to an assassin, a world conspiracy, and his dead partner! (Source: Funimation) Note: The first episode aired with a runtime of ~46 minutes as opposed to the standard 24 minute long episode.
Isshou Hatarakitakunai Ore ga Classmate no Daininki Idol ni Natsukaretara

Rintaro Shido, a high school boy who aspires to be a full-time house-husband, is in the same class as Rei Otosaki, the center of the popular idol group "Millefeuille Stars." The two have never been involved with each other, until one day when Rei nearly collapses from hunger, and Rintaro makes a home-cooked meal to feed her.......

"I'll pay you 300,000-yen a month. Can I come and eat with you every day?"

Thus began their new relationship, almost like a couple living together. Rintaro is unable to grasp the proper distance between himself and Rei, who comes to his room where he lives alone. There, Rei shows a vulnerable side that she would never show in the classroom or on stage.......?

This is the start of a romantic comedy about a semi-cohabitation arrangement with a beautiful, popular idol girl, that will make your heart tingle and pound!

(Source: Over-Lap, translated)
Matching App de Moto Koibito to Saikai Shita.

Sho Fujigaya is a university student who has long since broken up with his girlfriend. On a matchmaking app he started on the recommendation of a friend, he found someone he could have a good conversation with. What's more, the app shows that their compatibility is 98%! A good opportunity to start a new relationship. But on the agreed date, the person who is at the meeting place is Hikaru Takamiya, his ex-girlfriend! They argue as they did back then, but regret and dissatisfaction seep into their hearts...
